This paper deals with the traveling salesman problem, which is a well-known combinatorial optimization problem. The paper focuses on the performance of meta-heuristics, specifically 2-opt based local search algorithms, for solving the TSP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), which deals with combinatorial optimization problems. The paper also uses a statistical approach to examine the features of TSP instances, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the success of the algorithm from a theoretical perspective, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.RO (Robotics).
